Product Management Supervisor






General Summary:
Seeking a motivated self-starter with strong interpersonal skills to assist in managing the quality control of information related to our company’s product offerings. In this role, you will primarily work with new and existing vendors on product launches, price updates and new product additions.
Essential Duties and Responsibilities include but are not limited to:

Direct liaison with vendors regarding product information and updates
Review product pricing and templates submitted by vendors to ensure accuracy
Responsible for confirming pricing schedules with management team
Maintain websites with updated skus and products, upon immediate receipt 
Ensure products are properly setup for all company divisions and world currencies
Consistently check for outdated products and maintain all default pricing



Requirements:

2-4 years in product management role 
Process-oriented personality who is proactive when it comes to problem solving and making decision calls, based on analytical findings and results
Comfortable with giving direction and interacting with all levels of executive team
Ability to be flexible and work in a dynamic and interactive team environment
Interested in building a career not simply finding a “job”
Highly proficient in EXCEL
Bachelor’s Degree preferred

Benefits:

Telecommuting opportunities
Flexible work schedule 
Medical and dental benefits 
401(k) Plan with company match
Business casual work environment
Amazing team of people who love what they do!

If you meet these requirements, please apply now.
This position description intends to describe the general nature and level of work being performed by people assigned to this job. It is not intended to include all duties and responsibilities. The order in which duties and responsibilities are listed is not significant.
Equal Opportunity Employer, M/F/D/V, drug-free work environment.




